design.name: Expansion Pack for vCenter
design.author: dongyun.heo
design.description:
API Information
Infrastructure JSON API
https://developer.broadcom.com/xapis/virtual-infrastructure-json-api/latest/

Tested Solutions
Aira Operations Management Pack Builder: 1.1.2.22157532
Aira Operations: 8.17.1.23642243
vCenter Server: 8.0.2.23319993

Requests
GET Folder/group-d1/childEntity
GET Datacenter/${datacenter_id}/hostFolder
GET Datacenter/${datacenter_id}/networkFolder
GET Folder/${host_folder_id}/childEntity
GET Folder/${network_folder_id}/childEntity
GET ClusterComputeResource/${cluster_id}/host
GET Folder/${child_folder_id}/childEntity
POST DistributedVirtualSwitch/${dvs_id}/FetchDVPorts
GET HostSystem/${host_id}/summary
GET HostSystem/${host_id}/configManager
GET HostNetworkSystem/${host_network_system_id}/networkInfo

Objects
[INTERNAL] Host System Standard Switch
[INTERNAL] Host System Distributed Switch
[INTERNAL] Distributed Virtual Switch Uplink Port
[INTERNAL] Folder Distributed Virtual Switch Uplink Port

Relationships
Host System -> Host System Standard Switch
Host System -> Host System Distributed Switch
Host System Distributed Switch -> Distributed Virtual Switch Uplink Port
Host System Distributed Switch -> Folder Distributed Virtual Switch Uplink Port

configuration.label: Hostname
configuration.description: The hostname or IP address use to connect to the target API.

configuration.label: Port
configuration.description: The port used to connect to the target API.

configuration.label: Connection Timeout (s)
configuration.description: The maximum number of seconds to wait for a response from the endpoint.

configuration.label: Max Concurrent Requests
configuration.description: The maximum number of requests that can be run simultaneously.

configuration.label: Maximum Retries
configuration.description: The maximum number of times a call to an edpoint will be retried if it fails.

configuration.label: SSL
configuration.description: The SSL mode to use when connecting to the target. Can be configured without SSL (No SSL), to use SSL, but do not verify the target's certificate (No Verify), or to use SSL and verify the target's certificate (Verify).

configuration.label: Minimum VMware Aria Operations Severity
configuration.description: The minimum event severity to collect.
